{
  "texts": [
    "For eROSITA, we can take advantage of the all-sky survey nature of the observations to build large samples that can be used to validate the flux calibration in a statistical sense.",
    "For point sources, we report here (Sect. 6.1) a comparison with XMM-Newton in the 0.5-2 keV band, resulting in a possible residual flux systematic uncertainty of just about 6%, similarly to what was found by Maitra et al.",
    "(2022) in the early phases of the mission.",
    "We have also tested the effect of possible PSF calibration uncertainties on the reconstructed flux, by running an alternative source detection pipeline which makes use of the PSF image preliminary stacks, and found only a 3% source counts systematic offset compared to the catalogue described here.The situation for clusters of galaxies in the survey is still under examination (but see e.g.",
    "Whelan et al."
  ]
}